cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with incorporating linguistic prior into neural machine translation. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a hybrid model that combines recurrent neural network grammar and attention-based neural machine translation. Additionally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks for both parsing and translation. Finally, it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it involves natural language processing, which is often used in conjunction with computer vision tasks.
